root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1499</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Requirement</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-006Y</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-006Y.xml</fr:route><fr:title>The <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/"
type="external">git</fr:link> distributed version control system</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>8</fr:month><fr:day>14</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>It is best practice to maintain your <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000R">forest</fr:link> inside of <fr:link
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distributed_version_control"
type="external">distributed version control</fr:link>. This serves not only as a way to prevent data loss (because you will be pushing frequently to a remote repository); it also allows you to easily roll back to an earlier version of your <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000R">forest</fr:link>, or to create “branches” in which you prepare <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000R">trees</fr:link> that are not yet ready to be integrated into the <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000R">forest</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p>The recommended <fr:link
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distributed_version_control"
type="external">distributed version control</fr:link> system is <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/"
type="external">git</fr:link>, which comes preinstalled on many unix-based systems and is easy to install otherwise. <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/"
type="external">Git</fr:link> is not the most user-friendly piece of software, unfortunately, but it is ubiquitous. It is possible (but not recommended) to use <fr:link
href="jms-005P.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-005P">Forester</fr:link> without version control, but note that the simplest way to <fr:link
href="jms-006X.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-006X">initialize your own <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000R">forest</fr:link></fr:link> involves cloning a <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/"
type="external">git</fr:link> repository.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:context><fr:related><fr:tree
